TITLE: Creating Custom Node Components with Vue Render Functions
DESCRIPTION: Examples of creating custom node components using Vue's render function (h). These components demonstrate scrollable node content and input field node implementations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bcakmakoglu/vue-flow/blob/master/docs/src/guide/node.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const ScrollableNode = () => h('div', { class: 'custom-node-container' }, [
  h('ul', { class: 'nowheel' }, Array.from({ length: 100 }, (_, i) => h('li', { key: i }, `Item ${i}`)))
]);

const InputFieldNode = () => h('div', { class: 'custom-node-container' }, [
  h('input', { class: 'nodrag placeholder-white', placeholder: 'Type something...' })
]);
```

