TITLE: Using isEdge Function with Vue Flow
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the isEdge function to check if an element is an edge and toggle CSS classes on edges specifically. This example creates a simple graph with two nodes connected by an edge, then provides a button to toggle between 'light' and 'dark' classes on the edges.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bcakmakoglu/vue-flow/blob/master/docs/src/guide/utils/graph.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: vue
CODE:
