TITLE: Configuring Vue Flow with ModelValue (Elements)
DESCRIPTION: Example showing the deprecated method of configuring Vue Flow using the modelValue prop with an array of elements combining both nodes and edges.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bcakmakoglu/vue-flow/blob/master/docs/src/guide/vue-flow/config.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: vue
CODE:
```
<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue'  
import { VueFlow } from '@vue-flow/core'

const elements = ref([
  { id: '1', type: 'input', label: 'Node 1', position: { x: 250, y: 5 } },
  { id: '2', label: 'Node 2', position: { x: 100, y: 100 }, },
  { id: '3', label: 'Node 3', position: { x: 400, y: 100 } },
  { id: '4', type: 'output', label: 'Node 4', position: { x: 400, y: 200 } },
  { id: 'e1-3', source: '1', target: '3' },
  { id: 'e1-2', source: '1', target: '2', animated: true },
])
</script>

<template>
  <VueFlow v-model="elements" />
</template>
```

